  "buggy_files": ["sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["azx_stop_chip"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The polling_mode flag is set to 1 when codec communication times out in azx_rirb_get_response(), but it is never reset to 0. After suspend/resume cycles, when azx_stop_chip() disables the chip and sets chip->initialized to 0, the polling_mode flag remains set. During resume, azx_init_chip() reinitializes the hardware but does not reset polling_mode, causing the driver to stay in polling mode even though the hardware has been reset. This leads to codec communication failures manifesting as choppy sound with clicks separated by 2-second silences. The fix is to add 'chip->polling_mode = 0;' in azx_stop_chip() to reset the transient polling mode state when the chip is shut down, ensuring a clean state when the chip is reinitialized during resume."
}

